00:03:11.526 --> 00:03:12.994 position:30% line:89% align:start
Hm?

00:03:13.027 --> 00:03:15.697 position:33% line:89% align:start
[ Rattling ]

00:03:15.730 --> 00:03:18.298 position:33% line:89% align:start
Enju? Kaede?

00:03:18.331 --> 00:03:20.300 position:41% line:83% align:start
-Uh-oh.
-[ Gasps ] Makaba?

00:03:20.333 --> 00:03:22.003 position:30% line:77% align:start
[ Door opens ]
Hmm?

00:03:22.036 --> 00:03:23.303 position:52% line:89% align:start
Karin: Huh?

00:03:23.336 --> 00:03:25.506 position:41% line:83% align:start
What are you doing
out here, Makaba?

00:03:25.540 --> 00:03:27.441 position:61% line:83% align:start
Ugh.
The ants are here, too.

00:03:27.474 --> 00:03:29.177 position:44% line:83% align:start
-Hey!
-Seriously, Karin?

00:03:29.209 --> 00:03:30.778 position:19% line:83% align:start
Just what do you think
you're doing up her--

00:03:30.812 --> 00:03:33.380 position:44% line:83% align:start
Huh?!
What the heck?!

00:03:37.250 --> 00:03:39.419 position:33% line:83% align:start
Hearing Kei was coming
had us pretty rattled.

00:03:39.453 --> 00:03:41.022 position:16% line:83% align:start
But our minds
are made up!

00:03:41.055 --> 00:03:43.624 position:13% line:83% align:start
Kaede and Enju: We're gonna
go rescue Yukimaru and Fena!

00:03:43.658 --> 00:03:46.094 position:47% line:83% align:start
Well, for once,
I agree with them.

00:03:46.127 --> 00:03:48.096 position:47% line:83% align:start
Yukimaru can't
pull this off alone.

00:03:48.129 --> 00:03:50.363 position:38% line:83% align:start
Then I can make that
crusty old ginger pay

00:03:50.397 --> 00:03:51.866 position:50% line:83% align:start
for attacking
my beautiful face!

00:03:51.899 --> 00:03:54.102 position:5% line:83% align:start
Tsubaki: That's the <i>real</i> reason
you're really going.

00:03:54.135 --> 00:03:55.469 position:35% line:83% align:start
-Hey, uh...
-Huh?

00:03:55.503 --> 00:03:57.772 position:7% line:83% align:start
If we're all going,
it might be better

00:03:57.805 --> 00:04:02.210 position:5% line:83% align:start
if we went in the <i>Bonito</i> and not
the little boat, don't ya think?

00:04:02.242 --> 00:04:04.579 position:44% line:83% align:start
Oh, yeah. Hadn't
thought of that.

00:04:04.612 --> 00:04:06.013 position:35% line:89% align:start
Good point.

00:04:06.047 --> 00:04:08.182 position:10% line:83% align:start
This plan is all
well and good, but...

00:04:08.216 --> 00:04:09.684 position:5% line:89% align:start
there's still Shitan.

00:04:09.717 --> 00:04:11.919 position:5% line:83% align:start
Of all his annoying traits,
his rule-following is...

00:04:11.953 --> 00:04:13.855 position:44% line:89% align:start
Shitan: Is what?

00:04:18.826 --> 00:04:20.828 position:44% line:83% align:start
Gah!
S-S-Shitan?!

00:04:22.429 --> 00:04:24.532 position:24% line:89% align:start
Uh, hey. We, uh...

00:04:24.565 --> 00:04:27.702 position:7% line:83% align:start
Shitan! Okay. So, hear me out.
I came up with this great plan.

00:04:27.735 --> 00:04:29.336 position:21% line:77% align:start
All we gotta do is --
Do whatever you like.

00:04:29.369 --> 00:04:32.940 position:44% line:77% align:start
Uh...
I'm returning.

00:04:32.974 --> 00:04:34.876 position:27% line:89% align:start
B-But, Shitan...

00:04:34.909 --> 00:04:39.781 position:64% line:5% align:start
♪♪

00:04:39.814 --> 00:04:42.583 position:30% line:83% align:start
Do you remember
why you took up the bow?

00:04:42.617 --> 00:04:45.586 position:21% line:77% align:start
What was the reason?
Hmm?

00:04:45.620 --> 00:04:47.588 position:38% line:83% align:start
The bows that I make
are stiff.

00:04:47.622 --> 00:04:49.824 position:52% line:83% align:start
The arrows
don't fly straight.

00:04:49.857 --> 00:04:53.027 position:47% line:83% align:start
And most people
didn't want to use them.

00:04:53.060 --> 00:04:55.696 position:44% line:83% align:start
But then one day,
 <i>you</i> did.

00:04:55.730 --> 00:04:58.431 position:41% line:83% align:start
What you said to me
was this --

00:04:58.465 --> 00:05:00.101 position:33% line:89% align:start
"It's amazing, Makaba.

00:05:00.134 --> 00:05:03.538 position:21% line:83% align:start
With a bow like this, I'll
be able to keep Yukimaru safe."

00:05:03.571 --> 00:05:04.872 position:16% line:89% align:start
Hmm...

00:05:06.473 --> 00:05:09.243 position:21% line:89% align:start
Do you remember that?

00:05:09.277 --> 00:05:11.813 position:21% line:83% align:start
We have fought a lot
of battles together.

00:05:11.846 --> 00:05:16.316 position:7% line:83% align:start
And how many times now have you
saved Yukimaru with your arrows?

00:05:16.349 --> 00:05:19.787 position:13% line:83% align:start
Yukimaru has saved my life.
And Tsubaki, too.

00:05:21.388 --> 00:05:24.692 position:16% line:89% align:start
We made a kind of circle.

00:05:24.725 --> 00:05:28.296 position:16% line:83% align:start
Then the twins and Karin
showed up,

00:05:28.328 --> 00:05:31.666 position:13% line:89% align:start
and our circle grew bigger.

00:05:31.699 --> 00:05:36.137 position:24% line:5% align:start
And now Fena is our
newest member to join,

00:05:36.170 --> 00:05:38.840 position:7% line:5% align:start
making our circle even bigger.

00:05:38.873 --> 00:05:42.009 position:30% line:5% align:start
I may be wrong,
but I think that's a good thing.

00:05:42.043 --> 00:05:45.378 position:27% line:89% align:start
[ Wind whistles ]

00:05:45.412 --> 00:05:46.914 position:55% line:89% align:start
Shitan...

00:05:46.948 --> 00:05:50.952 position:19% line:83% align:start
the rest of us are going to
save Yukimaru and Fena.

00:05:50.985 --> 00:05:54.222 position:19% line:83% align:start
And not because of our code
or some ulterior motive,

00:05:54.255 --> 00:05:57.892 position:24% line:83% align:start
but because they're
our friends, our circle.

00:05:57.925 --> 00:06:01.229 position:38% line:89% align:start
You know?

00:06:01.262 --> 00:06:02.897 position:64% line:89% align:start
Shitan...

00:06:02.930 --> 00:06:08.102 position:64% line:5% align:start
♪♪

00:06:08.135 --> 00:06:13.140 position:64% line:5% align:start
♪♪

00:06:13.174 --> 00:06:16.177 position:35% line:83% align:start
When he's on his own,
Yukimaru gets into trouble.

00:06:16.210 --> 00:06:17.945 position:47% line:89% align:start
You know that.

00:06:19.714 --> 00:06:24.619 position:41% line:83% align:start
And saving Yukimaru
is your role, isn't it?

00:06:24.652 --> 00:06:26.921 position:47% line:83% align:start
Let's save him
together.

00:06:26.954 --> 00:06:33.127 position:64% line:5% align:start
♪♪

00:06:33.160 --> 00:06:39.367 position:64% line:5% align:start
♪♪

00:06:39.399 --> 00:06:43.104 position:21% line:89% align:start
Fena: This person...

00:06:43.137 --> 00:06:45.172 position:33% line:89% align:start
is my mother?

00:06:45.206 --> 00:06:47.275 position:64% line:5% align:start
♪♪

00:06:47.308 --> 00:06:49.911 position:5% line:89% align:start
Helena des Armoises.

00:06:49.944 --> 00:06:54.548 position:5% line:83% align:start
And this portrait of her
is the only remaining image.

00:06:54.582 --> 00:06:56.384 position:38% line:89% align:start
I painted it myself.

00:06:56.416 --> 00:06:58.953 position:41% line:89% align:start
 <i>You</i> painted this?

00:06:58.986 --> 00:07:02.690 position:5% line:83% align:start
Actually, I'm not finished
with it yet.

00:07:02.723 --> 00:07:06.493 position:5% line:83% align:start
It's based on hazy memories
from when I was a boy.

00:07:06.527 --> 00:07:09.830 position:13% line:83% align:start
But regardless
of the colors I apply...

00:07:09.864 --> 00:07:12.767 position:16% line:83% align:start
or how deftly
I wield my brush...

00:07:12.800 --> 00:07:16.837 position:5% line:83% align:start
I'm unable to capture
even half of her beauty.

00:07:16.871 --> 00:07:20.308 position:7% line:83% align:start
And those memories
are fading.

00:07:20.341 --> 00:07:23.311 position:16% line:83% align:start
Slowly, she's
slipping away from me.

00:07:23.344 --> 00:07:30.184 position:64% line:5% align:start
♪♪

00:07:30.217 --> 00:07:37.091 position:64% line:5% align:start
♪♪

00:07:37.124 --> 00:07:38.859 position:55% line:89% align:start
[ Gasps ]

00:07:38.893 --> 00:07:43.431 position:64% line:5% align:start
♪♪

00:07:43.463 --> 00:07:46.534 position:41% line:83% align:start
You were...in love
with my mother.

00:07:46.567 --> 00:07:49.103 position:47% line:89% align:start
Is that right?

00:07:49.136 --> 00:07:52.273 position:52% line:89% align:start
And, uh...

00:07:52.306 --> 00:07:55.475 position:7% line:89% align:start
do you know if...?

00:07:55.509 --> 00:07:57.912 position:10% line:89% align:start
Did she love <i>you?</i>

00:08:00.480 --> 00:08:02.550 position:10% line:89% align:start
[ Indistinct conversations ]

00:08:02.583 --> 00:08:05.353 position:24% line:89% align:start
[ Wind whistling ]

00:08:05.386 --> 00:08:07.421 position:38% line:89% align:start
[ Gasps ]

00:08:07.455 --> 00:08:09.489 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:08:13.160 --> 00:08:14.628 position:41% line:89% align:start
What's the matter?

00:08:14.662 --> 00:08:18.099 position:5% line:83% align:start
It's the <i>Rumble Rose,</i> Sir.
She's coming back.

00:08:18.132 --> 00:08:26.040 position:64% line:5% align:start
♪♪

00:08:26.073 --> 00:08:33.781 position:64% line:5% align:start
♪♪

00:08:33.814 --> 00:08:36.250 position:47% line:83% align:start
I just have to
know the truth.

00:08:38.019 --> 00:08:40.988 position:58% line:89% align:start
Helena.

00:08:41.022 --> 00:08:44.425 position:41% line:89% align:start
Did Helena love me?

00:08:44.458 --> 00:08:47.695 position:30% line:83% align:start
If so, then why did she
take you and --

00:08:47.728 --> 00:08:51.999 position:44% line:83% align:start
Aah!
What's going on?!

00:08:52.033 --> 00:08:54.969 position:19% line:89% align:start
Oh, she's opened fire!

00:08:55.002 --> 00:08:57.171 position:21% line:89% align:start
[ Gasps ]

00:08:57.204 --> 00:08:58.906 position:55% line:89% align:start
[ Gasps ]

00:09:01.208 --> 00:09:03.044 position:33% line:89% align:start
[ Rumbling ]

00:09:05.913 --> 00:09:07.214 position:58% line:89% align:start
Helena.

00:09:07.248 --> 00:09:09.150 position:21% line:89% align:start
[ Gasps ]

00:09:09.183 --> 00:09:12.953 position:19% line:89% align:start
[ Panting ] Lord Abel!

00:09:15.322 --> 00:09:16.657 position:24% line:89% align:start
What's the matter?

00:09:16.690 --> 00:09:18.692 position:44% line:83% align:start
The <i>Rumble Rose!</i>
They...

00:09:18.726 --> 00:09:20.561 position:47% line:83% align:start
They've turned
their ship around, sir!

00:09:20.594 --> 00:09:22.863 position:47% line:83% align:start
And now they're
firing on us!

00:09:22.897 --> 00:09:24.465 position:44% line:89% align:start
Fire!

00:09:24.498 --> 00:09:31.439 position:64% line:5% align:start
♪♪

00:09:31.472 --> 00:09:34.175 position:30% line:89% align:start
[ Cannon fire ]

00:09:34.208 --> 00:09:35.910 position:55% line:83% align:start
What are
your orders, sir?

00:09:35.943 --> 00:09:39.046 position:27% line:83% align:start
I would like you
to remain here.

00:09:39.080 --> 00:09:40.981 position:24% line:89% align:start
I will return soon.

00:09:41.015 --> 00:09:46.120 position:64% line:5% align:start
♪♪

00:09:46.153 --> 00:09:51.258 position:64% line:5% align:start
♪♪

00:09:51.292 --> 00:09:53.761 position:33% line:83% align:start
-Her status?
-She's closing in.

00:09:53.794 --> 00:09:56.730 position:5% line:83% align:start
Raise sail. Port rudder.
Turn 45 degrees.

00:09:56.764 --> 00:09:58.699 position:44% line:89% align:start
Right away, sir!

00:10:01.435 --> 00:10:03.938 position:35% line:83% align:start
Come about!
45 degrees, men!

00:10:03.971 --> 00:10:06.140 position:5% line:83% align:start
Crewman: Come about!
45 degrees!

00:10:06.173 --> 00:10:08.543 position:24% line:83% align:start
Crewman #2: Coming about!
45 degrees!

00:10:08.577 --> 00:10:10.945 position:64% line:5% align:start
♪♪

00:10:10.978 --> 00:10:13.481 position:5% line:83% align:start
My best guess is they plan
to use covering fire

00:10:13.515 --> 00:10:15.783 position:7% line:83% align:start
to get close enough
to board us, sir.

00:10:15.816 --> 00:10:18.587 position:5% line:83% align:start
The only advantage their ship
has over us is speed.

00:10:18.652 --> 00:10:20.988 position:19% line:83% align:start
Like flies
swarming to the spoils.

00:10:21.021 --> 00:10:23.558 position:41% line:83% align:start
Load the Wellington
with an explosive round.

00:10:23.592 --> 00:10:24.959 position:21% line:89% align:start
Sir?

00:10:24.992 --> 00:10:27.328 position:5% line:83% align:start
Not to overstep my bounds,
but that's a new weapon

00:10:27.361 --> 00:10:29.930 position:5% line:83% align:start
that was developed to breach
the walls of Saint-Malo.

00:10:29.964 --> 00:10:31.899 position:35% line:83% align:start
It's hardly something
that's appropriate

00:10:31.932 --> 00:10:33.968 position:41% line:83% align:start
for a lone, rickety
pirate ship.

00:10:34.001 --> 00:10:35.302 position:19% line:89% align:start
Captain...

00:10:35.336 --> 00:10:36.904 position:50% line:89% align:start
[ Grumbles ]

00:10:36.937 --> 00:10:39.574 position:58% line:83% align:start
Prepare
the Wellington cannon!

00:10:39.608 --> 00:10:41.976 position:27% line:89% align:start
Load an explosive round!

00:10:42.009 --> 00:10:48.649 position:64% line:5% align:start
♪♪

00:10:48.682 --> 00:10:55.557 position:64% line:5% align:start
♪♪

00:10:55.590 --> 00:10:57.592 position:35% line:83% align:start
Those ships
were sailing together,

00:10:57.626 --> 00:10:59.426 position:16% line:89% align:start
and now they're fighting.

00:10:59.460 --> 00:11:03.097 position:64% line:5% align:start
♪♪

00:11:03.130 --> 00:11:06.433 position:16% line:83% align:start
Has the balance of power
broken down?

00:11:06.467 --> 00:11:09.170 position:30% line:89% align:start
What caused it?

00:11:09.203 --> 00:11:11.606 position:21% line:89% align:start
Something's happened.

00:11:11.640 --> 00:11:13.874 position:13% line:83% align:start
The <i>Blue Giant</i>
is coming back around!

00:11:13.908 --> 00:11:15.843 position:44% line:83% align:start
Are they showing
their flank?

00:11:15.876 --> 00:11:18.513 position:5% line:5% align:start
Actually, it looks like
they want a tête-à-tête.

00:11:18.547 --> 00:11:20.649 position:55% line:83% align:start
Well now,
this should be fun.

00:11:20.681 --> 00:11:23.250 position:5% line:83% align:start
We'll show them what happens
to those foolish enough

00:11:23.284 --> 00:11:25.520 position:7% line:89% align:start
to get in our way.

00:11:25.554 --> 00:11:27.321 position:61% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:11:27.354 --> 00:11:29.591 position:50% line:89% align:start
[ Grumbles ]

00:11:29.624 --> 00:11:33.628 position:64% line:5% align:start
♪♪

00:11:33.662 --> 00:11:35.896 position:27% line:83% align:start
I've never seen a cannon
that massive before.

00:11:35.930 --> 00:11:37.464 position:33% line:89% align:start
What the hell is that?

00:11:37.498 --> 00:11:38.866 position:5% line:89% align:start
We're ready to fire.

00:11:38.899 --> 00:11:40.868 position:5% line:77% align:start
You should brace yourself.
Fire.

00:11:40.901 --> 00:11:44.238 position:21% line:83% align:start
Now full speed ahead!
We're going in!

00:11:44.271 --> 00:11:46.508 position:30% line:89% align:start
Captain: Fire!

00:11:46.541 --> 00:11:51.145 position:64% line:5% align:start
♪♪

00:11:51.178 --> 00:11:55.584 position:64% line:5% align:start
♪♪

00:11:55.617 --> 00:11:58.587 position:33% line:89% align:start
[ Screaming ]

00:11:58.620 --> 00:12:00.589 position:5% line:89% align:start
Unh! What's going on?!

00:12:00.622 --> 00:12:03.157 position:27% line:89% align:start
[ All grunting ]

00:12:03.190 --> 00:12:05.226 position:27% line:89% align:start
Aah!

00:12:05.259 --> 00:12:07.361 position:41% line:89% align:start
What is happening?!

00:12:07.394 --> 00:12:09.531 position:13% line:89% align:start
This can't be.

00:12:09.564 --> 00:12:11.732 position:33% line:89% align:start
[ Grunting ]

00:12:11.765 --> 00:12:18.973 position:64% line:5% align:start
♪♪

00:12:19.006 --> 00:12:20.207 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:12:20.241 --> 00:12:29.083 position:64% line:5% align:start
♪♪

00:12:29.116 --> 00:12:30.384 position:44% line:89% align:start
Abel.

00:12:30.417 --> 00:12:32.219 position:35% line:89% align:start
[ Growls ]

00:12:37.491 --> 00:12:39.260 position:21% line:89% align:start
[ Gasps ]

00:12:40.562 --> 00:12:42.429 position:44% line:89% align:start
Fena!

